summary: Aaron Rodgers made his first home start since returning from injury and led the New York Jets to a resounding 24-3 victory over the New England Patriots. The Jets dominated the game from start to finish, with Rodgers throwing for 252 yards and two touchdowns. The Jets' defense also played a key role in the win, holding the Patriots to just three points and forcing three turnovers. The victory is a significant boost to the Jets' hopes of making a playoff run, while the Patriots' third loss of the season puts their own playoff hopes in jeopardy. It was a dream come true for the Jets, as Rodgers played magnificently and helped the team blast the Patriots on Thursday Night Football.

name: Menendez brothers
summary: The Menendez Brothers case, which shocked the nation in the early 1990s, has recently been revisited in a new Netflix series. Erik and Lyle Menendez, two wealthy Beverly Hills brothers, murdered their parents in 1989. The trial was highly publicized, and the brothers were eventually convicted and sentenced to life in prison. In the aftermath of the crime, the therapist who had been treating the brothers, Leslie Abramson, became a key figure in the case. The Netflix series explores the brothers' story, including the role Abramson played in their defense. Additionally, the series examines the life of Kitty Menendez, the brothers' mother, who was a prominent figure in the Los Angeles society. Critics have praised the performances in the series but have criticized the overall story as lacking substance.
